{"questionId":"9419","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, or otherwise, show that the exact value of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}} = 2 - \\sqrt 3 \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>METHOD 1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = {\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x =&nbsp; - {\\text{cot}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cot</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> are roots of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^2} + \\left( {2\\,{\\text{cot}}\\frac{\\pi }{{6}}} \\right)x - 1 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>cot</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>6</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>R1</strong> </em>if only&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = {\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}}\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is stated as a root of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^2} + \\left( {2\\,{\\text{cot}}\\frac{\\pi }{{6}}} \\right)x - 1 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>cot</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>6</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^2} + 2\\sqrt 3 x - 1 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempting to solve <strong>their</strong> quadratic equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x =&nbsp; - \\sqrt 3&nbsp; \\pm 2\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mo>±</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}} > 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - {\\text{cot}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}} < 0\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>cot</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}} = 2 - \\sqrt 3 \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>METHOD 2</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempting to substitute&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\theta&nbsp; = \\frac{\\pi }{{12}}\">\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> into the identity for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\,2\\theta \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{6} = \\frac{{2\\,{\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}}}}{{1 - {\\text{ta}}{{\\text{n}}^2}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mn>6</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>tan</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>12</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>ta</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>n</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>π</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>12</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{ta}}{{\\text{n}}^2}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}} + 2\\sqrt 3 \\,{\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}} - 1 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>ta</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>n</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempting to solve <strong>their </strong>quadratic equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}} =&nbsp; - \\sqrt 3&nbsp; \\pm 2\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n  <mo>±</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}} > 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\frac{\\pi }{{12}} = 2 - \\sqrt 3 \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9419","referenceCode":"SPM.2.AHL.TZ0.12c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, or otherwise, show that the exact value of tan π 12 = 2 − 3 .","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.9—Reciprocal trig ratios and their pythagorean identities. Inverse circular functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Compound angle identities","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}